data.title: Trulieve's 2025 results: $1.2B revenue, 60% gross margin, $273M cash flow, 50.1M products sold, 11 dispensaries added. CEO optimistic for 2026.
data.description: Trulieve Cannabis Corp reported strong financial results for 2025, with a full-year revenue of $1.2 billion and a 60% gross margin. The company achieved record cash flow from operations of $273 million and free cash flow of $229 million in 2025. They sold a record 50.1 million branded product units, a 5% increase from the previous year. The company also reported a net loss attributable to common shareholders of $116 million. They closed a $140 million private placement of senior secured notes due 2030 and granted conditional approval for a Dispensing Organization license in Texas. Trulieve CEO, Kim Rivers, expressed optimism for 2026, focusing on expanded access, customer loyalty, branded products, and growth initiatives. The company operates 234 dispensaries and over four million square feet of cultivation and processing capacity in the U.S.

data.title: Bouygues selects Buildots to monitor construction of 44,000 m² logistics platform in Val-d'Oise using AI.
data.description: In Paris on February 26, 2026, Bouygues Bâtiment Industrie, a subsidiary of Bouygues Construction specializing in industrial projects, announced its partnership with Buildots, an AI-based construction progress monitoring tool. This collaboration will aid in the development of the P3 Persan project, covering an area of 44,000 square meters.

data.title: Bilt introduces Neighborhood Concierge service to handle various tasks for members in largest home network, rewarding millions monthly.
data.description: In a recent announcement, Bilt Founder and CEO Ankur Jain addressed Bilt Members in a letter, highlighting the evolution of the service into a comprehensive membership program designed to manage various aspects of home and neighborhood life. Over the past five years, Bilt has expanded to become the largest network of homes in the nation, offering rewards to millions of members monthly, particularly on rent and mortgage payments. This transformation has effectively imbued the concept of housing with a newfound level of benefits for the residents.

data.title: AEON releases 2025 payment data, showcasing growth of AI-native payments in new economy, highlighting demand for AI-native and crypto-based payment infrastructure.
data.description: In Hong Kong on February 26, 2026, AEON, a key payment and settlement platform for the evolving AI economy, has unveiled its payment performance data for 2025. The data underscores the increasing need for AI-integrated and cryptocurrency-driven payment systems. As the year concluded in 2025, AEON experienced a significant rise in demand, showcasing a shift towards AI-centric financial mechanisms.

data.title: Flowco Holdings Inc. (NYSE: FLOC) reports Q4 and full year 2025 results for oil and gas industry solutions.
data.description: Houston-based company Flowco Holdings Inc. (NYSE: FLOC) recently disclosed their financial results for Q4 and the entire year ending on December 31, 2025. Flowco specializes in offering production optimization, artificial lift, and emissions management services for the oil and natural gas sector. The figures for 2024 mentioned in the report are from a time when their operating subsidiary, Flowco MergeCo LLC (“Flowco LLC”), was privately owned.
